ฺฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฟ
   SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS
ภฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤู

    386/486/Pentium
    MS-DOS 3.3
    2+ MEGs RAM
    VGA graphics
    MS-compatible mouse
    SB or compatible (optional)



ฺฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฟ
   RULES
ภฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤู

     The object of MORPHELLO is to gain a majority of pieces on the
     playing board.  The score is kept on the top of the screen.
     Opponent pieces may be morphed into your own pieces by "capping"
     both ends of a contiguous row of opponent pieces.  This row may
     be in any 8 directions.  Moves that cause the surrounding of
     opponent pieces are the only valid moves, and if no valid moves
     exist the player's turn is forfeit.  The game ends when the board
     is full or neither player can make a move.



ฺฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฟ
   INSTRUCTIONS
ภฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤฤู

     From the main menu, set up the game by choosing players.  Higher
     intelligence levels may require some time to take their turn on
     slower computers.

     Registered owners of MORPHELLO can select their board from the
     available list.

     Select 'New' to begin playing.

     During the game you can return to the main menu by left-clicking
     anywhere off the board.  The game can be returned to by clicking
     'Resume'.

     The 'Save' button can be employed to store a copy of the game on
     disk (only one save bank is available).  'Load' will restore the
     saved game. 'Quit' returns to DOS.

     Inside the game, right-clicking will cause a 90 degree rotation
     of all the pieces on the board for improved visibility.

     Simply move the mouse to the desired location and click to make
     your move.


